Whether you are bringing the family for dinner, checking out the comedy cabaret, or just hanging out at the bar, we want you to come celebrate our 25th anniversary with us all year long!

Company Description

It sounds like the start of a joke, but it isn't. Keeping Chattanooga entertained for the last 25 years has been serious business for Michael and Cheryl Alfano. In the summer of 1985 The Comedy Catch debuted as Chattanooga's first full time comedy club, then located in Dr. Sages atop the since demolished Holiday Inn downtown. Comedians Kens Sons and Les McCurdy started the club but soon relocated the club to its present Brainerd Road location and was renamed The Comedy Catch at the Cafe. Being comedians they missed touring and performing comedy nation wide and decided to sell the Brainerd Rd business to Alfano's It was a rather small and intimate club back then ; seating about 100 ; with the restaurant, now named, Giggles Grill downstairs and the Show Room upstairs. Improvements over the years boosted the clubs' seating capacity to around 150 until the Great Remodel of 2000 transformed The Comedy Catch into the jewel it is today. The club is now all on one level and our Show Room can comfortably seat 250 with state of the art sound and lighting. One thing that hasn't changed in the last 25 years is the hands on ownership of the Alfano's, delicious food and beverages, and the best service staff in town. In its history The Comedy Catch has hosted some of the biggest stars in comedy. Names such as Jerry Seinfeld, Jeff Foxworthy, Ron White, D.L Hugley, Tommy Chong, Paula Poundstone, Tommy Davidson, Richard Jeni, Bobby Collins, Carrot Top, Tracy Morgan, Gallagher, James Gregory, Pauly Shore, Bobcat Goldthwait and many others have all graced our stage. In addition to national talent, The Comedy Catch stage has launched many local careers, and is considered one of the best venues in the south by many of the regional favorites. We start celebrating 25 wonderful years with the hope that we can bring 25 more years of Chattanooga's Most Fun Night Out!

Zanies carries a huge selection of single stick and packaged incense, sage, aromatherapy oils and body jewelry galore with the best prices in town. It's your one stop hippy shop! We're also one of the most unique gift shops in Spokane. Shop for men's and women's NFL licensed shirts, regular and tie dyed, with sizes up to 4x! We carry life-like prints from the mountain, tapestries, sarongs, flags, posters as well as calendars to decorate your home and office. Our selection of pipes includes metals, fimo, antler and hardwoods. Founded in 1984, ComedySportz is a theater group that hosts comedy shows for people of all age groups. Its players are paid professionals trained in special workshops and classes. The group plays improvisational comedies that involve a group of performers making up scenes and playing games on the spot based on audience suggestions. ComedySportz s hosts matches that feature the two teams of comedy actletes. It plays 7 to 12 games during a match. The group s players perform on-the-spot rap and comedy sequences. ComedySportz also serves a selection of pizzas, nachos and appetizers to audience. It maintains locations throughout the United States. The group is an independently owned businesses licensed by World Comedy League.
